---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import CTABlock from '../../components/CTABlock.astro';
import { business, BASE } from '../../data/business';
import { postBySlug, postsBySlugs, RELATED_POSTS } from '../../data/posts';
import RelatedPosts from '../../components/RelatedPosts.astro';
import BlogHero from '../../components/BlogHero.astro';
import BlogFigure from '../../components/BlogFigure.astro';

const post = postBySlug('handyman-ayrshire-landlords')!;
const relatedPosts = postsBySlugs(RELATED_POSTS[post.slug] ?? []).slice(0, 3);
const siteUrl = business.siteUrl.replace(/\/$/, '');
const url = `${siteUrl}/blog/${post.slug}/`;
const ogImage = `${siteUrl}${BASE}/gallery/ayrshire-living-room-emulsion-painting-18-1600w.jpg`;

const articleSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Article',
  '@id': `${url}#article`,
  headline: post.title,
  description: post.description,
  inLanguage: 'en-GB',
  datePublished: post.date,
  dateModified: post.date,
  author: {
    '@type': 'Person',
    name: post.author,
    worksFor: { '@id': `${siteUrl}/#business` },
  },
  publisher: { '@id': `${siteUrl}/#business` },
  image: [ogImage],
  mainEntityOfPage: url,
  articleSection: 'Landlord & property maintenance',
  keywords: [post.keyword, 'tenant turnover Kilmarnock', 'property maintenance KA postcodes', 'end of tenancy handyman', 'landlord contractor Ayrshire'],
  wordCount: post.wordCount,
  about: [{ '@type': 'Place', name: 'Ayrshire, Scotland' }],
};
---
<BaseLayout
  title={`${post.title} | Sorn Handyman Services`}
  description={post.description}
  canonicalPath={`/blog/${post.slug}/`}
  ogImage={ogImage}
  ogType="article"
  extraSchema={articleSchema}
>
  <Breadcrumbs trail={[
    { name: 'Home', href: `${BASE}/` },
    { name: 'Blog', href: `${BASE}/blog/` },
    { name: post.title },
  ]} />

  <article class="container-x py-10 lg:py-14 max-w-3xl">
    <header>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-amber-600">
        <span>{post.area}</span>
        <span aria-hidden class="text-navy-900/20">·</span>
        <span class="text-navy-900/60">{post.readMinutes} min read</span>
        <span aria-hidden class="text-navy-900/20">·</span>
        <time datetime={post.date} class="text-navy-900/60">{post.dateDisplay}</time>
      </div>
      <h1 class="mt-4 font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-navy-900 leading-tight">
        {post.title}
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-5 text-lg text-navy-900/75">
        If you let property in the KA postcodes, you already know half the job
        is maintenance on a deadline. This is the plain-English version of
        what we do for Ayrshire landlords — make-good packages, tenant-damage
        fixes, same-day response between tenancies, and the invoicing terms
        that actually work for portfolios.
      </p>
    </header>
    <BlogHero slug="ayrshire-living-room-emulsion-painting-18" />


    <div class="prose-sorn mt-8 text-lg cv-auto">
      <p>
        About a third of our weekly work across
        <a href={`${BASE}/areas/`}>East Ayrshire</a> is for landlords and
        letting agents. Some of them we have been working with for five years;
        some of them are a one-flat accidental landlord who just needs the
        keys back in a week. The jobs are the same — the paperwork is what
        changes.
      </p>
      <p>
        This post is the stuff letting agents and portfolio landlords ring
        to ask about anyway, written down in one place.
      </p>

      <h2>The end-of-tenancy make-good package</h2>
      <p>
        When a tenant moves out and the checkout report lands, you usually
        have a narrow window — often a week, sometimes less — to get the
        flat re-rentable. We do a <strong>standard make-good package</strong>
        for one-bed and two-bed rentals across Ayrshire that covers the
        fixes that show up on 90% of checkout reports:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Skirting boards re-fixed and touched up with satin white.</li>
        <li>Internal doors eased, hinges re-screwed, latches lubricated.</li>
        <li>
          Magnolia or white emulsion touch-up on scuffs, drilled holes filled
          and sanded flush.
        </li>
        <li>Bathroom silicone strip-out and re-bead, bath reseal.</li>
        <li>Kitchen unit doors re-aligned, broken soft-close hinges swapped.</li>
        <li>Lightbulbs and smoke-alarm batteries checked.</li>
        <li>Gutter and downpipe check on the exterior.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Every job priced individually against the checkout report. Send us
        the PDF or a photo list and we come back with a free no-obligation
        quote off it before we start — no "we found another thing" invoices
        at the end.
      </p>
      <p>
        For the full scope list on bigger properties, our
        <a href={`${BASE}/services/property-maintenance/`}>property
        maintenance page</a> has the package version. Most landlords
        combine a make-good with a full
        <a href={`${BASE}/services/painting-decorating/`}>repaint</a>
        every third or fourth tenancy, which is when it is cheapest to
        get the whole flat back to a photographable standard.
      </p>

            <div class="not-prose my-8">
        <BlogFigure slug="ayrshire-kitchen-refit-belfast-sink-granite-15" />
      </div>

      <h2>Tenant-damage fixes we do every week</h2>
      <p>
        Honest answer: the same dozen jobs, over and over, across
        <a href={`${BASE}/areas/kilmarnock/`}>Kilmarnock</a>,
        <a href={`${BASE}/areas/cumnock/`}>Cumnock</a>,
        <a href={`${BASE}/areas/mauchline/`}>Mauchline</a> and
        <a href={`${BASE}/areas/auchinleck/`}>Auchinleck</a>. If you see
        any of these on a checkout report, know that the fix is fast and
        boring:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Damaged skirting at corners</strong> — usually a hoover or
          a door wedge. Cut, splice, paint.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Internal door holes</strong> — door handle in the plaster,
          or a kick-through on a bathroom door. Lining-paper patch or full
          door swap.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Bathroom sealant gone black</strong> — strip out, clean
          down, re-bead with anti-mould.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Kitchen unit drawers off runners</strong> — re-hang or
          replace the soft-close mechanism.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Toilet seat hinges snapped</strong> — replaced like-for-like.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Paint scuffs, nail holes, picture-hook damage</strong> —
          filled, sanded, touched up. Part of the make-good package.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Loose or broken blinds and curtain poles</strong> — re-fixed
          or swapped.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Missing smoke-alarm covers / pulled-out wiring</strong> —
          we replace like-for-like on mains-linked alarms and leave the
          cert. For new circuit work we bring in a Part-P electrician —
          see the note at the end.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Every fix on that list is priced individually — phone or WhatsApp
        for a free no-obligation quote against your checkout report.
      </p>

      <h2>Same-day response for rent-ready deadlines</h2>
      <p>
        A tenant is moving in on Saturday and the checkout was Tuesday. This
        is the landlord panic call and we get a lot of them. If you ring us
        first thing Wednesday morning with a photo list, we can almost always
        get the flat done by Friday evening — and if the list is short we
        can do it the same day.
      </p>
      <p>
        How we make that work:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          You send a WhatsApp with the checkout PDF or a photo list.
          Fraser or Aidan reads it the same day.
        </li>
        <li>
          We come back with a free no-obligation quote inside the day — we
          are not adding VAT, there is no VAT on our invoices because we are
          under the threshold.
        </li>
        <li>
          We book into the next free slot — usually same or next day for
          anything under four hours in Kilmarnock, Cumnock, Mauchline,
          Auchinleck, Sorn and Catrine.
        </li>
        <li>
          We photograph the completed work and send the final invoice with
          before/after shots so your letting agent can sign off without a
          re-inspection.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Invoicing terms for portfolio landlords</h2>
      <p>
        We bill differently depending on scale:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>One or two flats:</strong> invoice on completion, payable
          by bank transfer or card link inside 7 days.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Three to ten flats:</strong> monthly consolidated invoice,
          30-day payment terms, itemised by property.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Letting agents and property-management companies:</strong>
          we accept your purchase-order workflow and invoice to the accounts
          email you nominate. Free no-obligation quote on every job across
          <a href={`${BASE}/areas/`}>our East Ayrshire patch</a>.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Everything goes through Stripe or bank transfer. No cash. Receipts
        are VAT-style even though we are not VAT-registered — so your
        accountant has a clean paper trail for each property.
      </p>

      <h2>The one thing we do not do: notifiable electrical work</h2>
      <p>
        We are not Part-P registered electricians. We swap like-for-like
        sockets, light fittings, cooker isolators and smoke alarms, but new
        circuits, consumer-unit work and anything notifiable in Scotland we
        bring in a local registered contractor for. We have a couple we
        trust and we will coordinate the visit so you still only deal with
        one of us.
      </p>

      <h2>FAQ</h2>
      <h3>Do you work with letting agents or only direct landlords?</h3>
      <p>
        Both. We have agents in Kilmarnock and Ayr who give us their whole
        turnover pipeline, and individual landlords with one to five
        properties each.
      </p>
      <h3>Do you do out-of-hours callouts for tenants?</h3>
      <p>
        Yes — a burst pipe, a broken lock, a flooding drain. We answer at
        any hour. Out-of-hours calls (10pm–6am) are priced individually —
        phone or WhatsApp for a free no-obligation quote before we set off.
        Send the tenant our WhatsApp number if it helps.
      </p>
      <h3>Can you hold a key for a property?</h3>
      <p>
        We do for some regular customers. Keys are labelled with postcode
        only (never the full address) and kept in a lockbox at the yard.
        Ask us if you want this set up.
      </p>
      <h3>Do you cover Ayr and Troon too?</h3>
      <p>
        Yes. We cover <a href={`${BASE}/areas/ayr/`}>Ayr</a>,
        <a href={`${BASE}/areas/troon/`}>Troon</a>,
        <a href={`${BASE}/areas/prestwick/`}>Prestwick</a>,
        <a href={`${BASE}/areas/irvine/`}>Irvine</a> and the rest of the KA
        postcodes as standard.
      </p>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 rounded-2xl border border-navy-900/10 bg-navy-50/50 p-6">
        <p class="text-sm text-navy-900/60">Written by</p>
        <p class="mt-1 font-serif text-xl font-bold text-navy-900">{post.author}</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-navy-900/75 text-sm">{post.authorBio}</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>

  <RelatedPosts posts={relatedPosts} eyebrow="Keep reading" heading="Related posts" variant="tinted" />

  <CTABlock
    heading="Turnover this week? Let's get it done."
    sub="Send the checkout report on WhatsApp. We'll read it, price it, and book you in — usually same or next day across the KA postcodes."
    location="Ayrshire"
  />
</BaseLayout>
